The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Friday, July 09, 2004 				 Axe on minister perks
New Delhi, July 8 (PTI): The Union government proposes to cut the provisions for salaries and tour expenses of ministers by reducing the budgetary grants.																								The budgetary provisions for the tour expenses have been put at Rs 46 crore  Rs 42 crore less compared to last years Rs 88 crore. 																								The salaries of cabinet ministers, minister of states and deputy ministers have been reduced to Rs 1.51 crore from the previous years Rs 2.91 crore. 																								The sumptuary and other allowances have also been reduced marginally from Rs 2.73 crore to Rs 2.55 crore. 
